⭐ Reputation Stress Test Tool
A CLI tool to perform stress testing on a reputation service by sending concurrent API requests.

📥 Installation
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone <your_repo_url>
cd SAMReputationTool
Install the package locally (editable mode):

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install -e .
🚀 How to Run a Stress Test
Use the reptest command with the following options:

bash
Copy
Edit
reptest --parallel-requests <number> --domains-num <number> --timeout <seconds> --log-level <level>
Example:
bash
Copy
Edit
reptest --parallel-requests 1000 --domains-num 50 --timeout 30 --log-level INFO
--parallel-requests: Number of concurrent requests to send.

--domains-num: Total number of different domains to test.

--timeout: Maximum duration of the test in seconds.

--log-level: Logging level (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR).

📂 Output
Logs and test results will be saved automatically in the logs/ folder.

After completion, logs and results are compressed into a .zip file.

🛠️ Requirements
Python 3.8+

Dependencies listed in requirements.txt
